<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,458,2033]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,458,484]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Husser" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[408,631,459,485]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Amazonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burgessi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[408,631,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Amazonius burgessi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[637,738,459,485]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[637,738,459,485]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[946,1049,459,485]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Tapinauchenius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elenae" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[946,1049,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">A. elenae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1055,1156,459,485]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1055,1156,459,485]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the multilobular spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[272,433,494,521]" captionStart="FIGURES 345–352" captionStartId="106.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,200,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-19@106.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 345–352. Amazonius burgessi n. comb. (345–348) male holotype (SMF 69513-84), left bulb (mirrored). 345, retrolateral. 346, prolateral. 347, frontal. 348, dorsal. (349–351) female (ICN-Ar 7530). 349, left maxilla (mirrored) showing lyra. 350, basal chelicerae showing strikers. 351, spermathecae. 352, female paratype (SMF 69514-84), spermathecae. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253472/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Figs 351–352</figureCitation>
). They can be distinguished by the modified short stiff setae on the ventral area of femur I (
<figureCitation box="[177,339,530,557]" captionStart="FIGURES 353–361" captionStartId="107.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-20@107.[160,1427,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURES 353–361. Setae on femur I, females. (353–354) Amazonius elenae n. comb. (MZUSP 37479). 353, left femur I, proventral. 354, same, detail of basal area. (355–356) Amazonius burgessi n. comb., paratype (SMF 69514-84). 355, femur I, proventral. 356, same, detail of basal area. (357–359) Amazonius giovaninii n. gen. n. sp., holotype (MNRJ 7715). 357, femur I, ventral. 358–359, same, detail of basal area. (360–361) Amazonius germani n.gen. n. sp., holotype (MPEG 007435). 360, femur I, proventral. 361, same, detail of basal area. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253474" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253474/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Figs 355–356</figureCitation>
). Males resemble those of 
<taxonomicName box="[647,794,531,557]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Amazonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giovaninii" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[647,794,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">A. giovaninii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[802,956,531,557]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[802,883,531,557]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
n. sp.
</emphasis>
by the male palpal bulb embolus roughly straight with a slight curvature distally (
<figureCitation box="[602,758,566,593]" captionStart="FIGURES 345–352" captionStartId="106.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,200,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-19@106.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 345–352. Amazonius burgessi n. comb. (345–348) male holotype (SMF 69513-84), left bulb (mirrored). 345, retrolateral. 346, prolateral. 347, frontal. 348, dorsal. (349–351) female (ICN-Ar 7530). 349, left maxilla (mirrored) showing lyra. 350, basal chelicerae showing strikers. 351, spermathecae. 352, female paratype (SMF 69514-84), spermathecae. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253472/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 345–348</figureCitation>
). They differ by the embolus tapering from its half in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[221,319,603,629]" captionStart="FIGURES 345–352" captionStartId="106.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,200,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-19@106.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 345–352. Amazonius burgessi n. comb. (345–348) male holotype (SMF 69513-84), left bulb (mirrored). 345, retrolateral. 346, prolateral. 347, frontal. 348, dorsal. (349–351) female (ICN-Ar 7530). 349, left maxilla (mirrored) showing lyra. 350, basal chelicerae showing strikers. 351, spermathecae. 352, female paratype (SMF 69514-84), spermathecae. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253472/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 348</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
