<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,458,2033]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,373,926,952]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Redescription.</emphasis>
Female (ICN-Ar-7530). Total length, not including chelicerae or spinnerets 31.40. Carapace 16.26 long, 13.68 wide, 8.04 high. Chelicera: 8.31 long. Legs (femur, patella, tibia, metatarsus, tarsus, total): I: 11.95, 7.49, 9.75, 8.77, 5.21, 43.17; II: 10.92, 6.69, 8.46, 8.45, 4.85, 39.37; III: 9.92, 5.89, 7.38, 8.53, 4.84, 36.56; IV: 12.16, 6.39, 10.26, 11.29, 4.71, 44.81; Palp: 8.33, 4.90, 5.63, -, 5.44, 24.3. Midwidths: femora I–IV= 2.43, 2.74, 2.76, 2.16, palp= 2.01; patellae I–IV= 2.72, 2.38, 2.70, 2.63, palp= 2.22; tibiae I–IV= 2.32, 2.14, 2.30, 2.50, palp= 2.13; metatarsi I–IV= 2.20, 1.97, 1.77, 1.66; tarsi I–IV= 1.99, 1.92, 1.85, 1.89, palp= 1.94. Abdomen: 15.16 long, 8.35 wide. Spinnerets: PMS, 1.78 long, 0.84 wide, 0.67 apart; PLS, 2.87 basal, 1.70 middle, 2.76 distal; midwidths 2.04, 1.91, 1.52, respectively. Carapace: 1.19 times longer than wide; cephalic region slightly raised, thoracic striae conspicuous. Fovea: deep, straight, 2.01 wide. Eyes: eye tubercle 1.24 high, 2.11 long, 3.60 wide. Clipeus: absent. Anterior eye row straight, posterior slightly recurved. Eye size and interdistances: AME 0.76, ALE 0.81, PME 0.42, PLE 0.65, AME–AME 0.56, AME–ALE 0.28, AME–PME 0.30, ALE–ALE 2.61, ALE–PME 0.55, PME–PME 1.92, PME–PLE 1.18, PLE–PLE 2.75, ALE–PLE 0.29. Maxilla: length to width 1.63. Cuspules: 141 spread over ventral inner heel. Labium: 2.09 long, 2.76 wide, with ca. 195 cuspules spaced by one diameter from each other on anterior third. Chelicera: basal segment with 10 teeth in row. Strikers: Long and short filiform setae, disposed without discernible pattern on a ventral-basal portion of chelicera before the teeth row (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1255,1430,1457]" captionStart="FIGURES 345–352" captionStartId="106.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,200,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-19@106.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 345–352. Amazonius burgessi n. comb. (345–348) male holotype (SMF 69513-84), left bulb (mirrored). 345, retrolateral. 346, prolateral. 347, frontal. 348, dorsal. (349–351) female (ICN-Ar 7530). 349, left maxilla (mirrored) showing lyra. 350, basal chelicerae showing strikers. 351, spermathecae. 352, female paratype (SMF 69514-84), spermathecae. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253472/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 350</figureCitation>
). Sternum: 7.80 long, 5.95 wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,458,2033]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
Legs: Formula: I = IV II III. Length leg IV to leg I: 1.04. Scopula: Tarsi I–IV fully scopulate; IV with a few sparse setae. Metatarsi I–II fully scopulate; III 1/2 distal; IV 1/3 distal. IV divided by rows of setae. Femora I ventrally and laterally with short scale like setae (
<figureCitation box="[669,829,1574,1601]" captionStart="FIGURES 353–361" captionStartId="107.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-20@107.[160,1427,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="107" captionText="FIGURES 353–361. Setae on femur I, females. (353–354) Amazonius elenae n. comb. (MZUSP 37479). 353, left femur I, proventral. 354, same, detail of basal area. (355–356) Amazonius burgessi n. comb., paratype (SMF 69514-84). 355, femur I, proventral. 356, same, detail of basal area. (357–359) Amazonius giovaninii n. gen. n. sp., holotype (MNRJ 7715). 357, femur I, ventral. 358–359, same, detail of basal area. (360–361) Amazonius germani n.gen. n. sp., holotype (MPEG 007435). 360, femur I, proventral. 361, same, detail of basal area. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253474" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253474/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Figs 355–356</figureCitation>
). Spination: Palps and legs (ventral apical: tibia/metatarsi): Palp 0; I: 0/0; II 2/0; III 1/0; IV 0/2. Maxillary stridulatory organ weakly developed, composed of slightly thick setae with rugose aspect, not disposed on an ordered line, grouped forming an oval patch on the prolateral face of the maxillae (
<figureCitation box="[334,433,1683,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 345–352" captionStartId="106.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,200,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-19@106.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 345–352. Amazonius burgessi n. comb. (345–348) male holotype (SMF 69513-84), left bulb (mirrored). 345, retrolateral. 346, prolateral. 347, frontal. 348, dorsal. (349–351) female (ICN-Ar 7530). 349, left maxilla (mirrored) showing lyra. 350, basal chelicerae showing strikers. 351, spermathecae. 352, female paratype (SMF 69514-84), spermathecae. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253472/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 349</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,458,2033]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
Spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[372,471,1718,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 345–352" captionStartId="106.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,200,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-19@106.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 345–352. Amazonius burgessi n. comb. (345–348) male holotype (SMF 69513-84), left bulb (mirrored). 345, retrolateral. 346, prolateral. 347, frontal. 348, dorsal. (349–351) female (ICN-Ar 7530). 349, left maxilla (mirrored) showing lyra. 350, basal chelicerae showing strikers. 351, spermathecae. 352, female paratype (SMF 69514-84), spermathecae. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253472/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 351</figureCitation>
): Two spermathecae completely separated, curved apically with an apical constriction forming lobes disposed as a crown, two striae from base to apex form a fold on ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,458,2033]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Color pattern (preserved in alcohol): Carapace and abdomen dark brown, legs and palpal femora brown with golden setae; tibia, metatarsus and tarsus brown.</paragraph>
