<paragraph blockId="108.[151,1437,1576,2035]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Legs: Formula I = IV II III, length leg IV to leg I: 0.96 (legs I missing, but see remarks below). Scopula: Tarsi II–IV fully scopulate; IV with a few sparse setae. Metatarsi II fully scopulate; III 2/3 distal; IV 1/3 distal. IV divided by rows of setae. Spination: Palps and legs (ventral apical: tibia/metatarsi): Palp 1/-; I: missing; II: 2/0; III 0/2; IV 0/2. Maxillary stridulatory organ: weakly developed, composed of slender setae with rugose aspect, not disposed on an ordered line, grouped forming an oval patch on the prolateral face of the maxillae. Tibial apophysis: two processes, retrolateral longer than prolateral, one spine at side of prolateral, one at apical part of retrolateral process. Metatarsus I folds on retrolateral side of tibial apophysis. Both holotype’s leg I missing (see remarks below).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="108.[151,1437,1576,2035]" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">
Palp (
<figureCitation box="[266,429,1828,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 345–352" captionStartId="106.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[211,1376,200,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-19@106.[211,1376,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURES 345–352. Amazonius burgessi n. comb. (345–348) male holotype (SMF 69513-84), left bulb (mirrored). 345, retrolateral. 346, prolateral. 347, frontal. 348, dorsal. (349–351) female (ICN-Ar 7530). 349, left maxilla (mirrored) showing lyra. 350, basal chelicerae showing strikers. 351, spermathecae. 352, female paratype (SMF 69514-84), spermathecae. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6253472" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6253472/files/figure.png" pageId="108" pageNumber="109">Figs 345–348</figureCitation>
